[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating object serialization**\n\nI’m thinking about how to assert that my writeObject output works by using `deserialize(serialize(activeKey))`. It seems like ObjectInputStream could tackle issues related to non-public classes and native image access. However, there’s a thought about failures due to the lack of a public no-argument constructor. Serializable classes shouldn’t need that, but I wonder if the superclass `Object` requires a no-arg constructor. Actually, it looks like it doesn’t. That's interesting!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0991db860aa0b9a0016a3fa3a7b77881979822c5651c834248\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP6PCNQabMDq34eHO9U0H7IbXrCHoQ870FF3u_V9HSDXz1XvJ5tC74YxVPMDAGNvFKMXijSR7rhzrMVA2kcddnSX-8IkmTU12PbTUUjjjfdRahN3oK5IYme2oxorFFiIe1YzQD1H_J_rE897dMtxPxyYsXzhbsrE8PDA5Fc8q7idDJ_3z1zEa4TSG7C1qmmOlP3n6Ym0MgYQxq149bE_MwaFlN0lpGtyLsWTwvTw1BGXmo96ZurqGWXBzSsQCbdh6rNocaKFy7UlGSyviEkueDpv1KYtPi9o5wRi1hxiZev8Yw65XMkAbtPBNvV1L-xcTLZ6FbNrNItHBuIVOmZSKGpaLfXsItEEtAyUMTbYBOIcuZRRXFpGf3mRYRmnD9pBqFvivSG343iu2c4nnW34dIMiXORYFvvGjvhKTghJbB9JhKZ6dC824a_pz0ngEu9TqAKi0h3Rj6BQVB5NsQLkSzwh1_UIF6u0H69-JJiDlyHMGYTiIRjRntZ6Q7-TWaXBmFyDdSjJUat0a2-ckSFrsmWDPRl9BVkmDTsHP64C9QZjq5GUNO3iVLAYgnzXDAzWW1Qsnu_Wr1BoR4zQVDU01Ioj2nz4kgTVwiyLsXT7Q7iy0m2iYRz4KOIGM37OAFwzwUXskYriFK3WIY2qQvC82JHCrXJOsIFUyoxAC8SHw0acWhsb2V-L-4hc8FxtTqcfg80po0HE4djGF4f6NKTBOFzUXr4e9KiGiy7yZBgHZ8psEVo05oFWXoMqvtRblyA8SAF69lzn5GLxhwqa8bflWG7BkNBmEd6kGLfi8kHjBJluAJIM7SYQ3YK8-MQTG3KGFlSBlrKBSKznFUt7w2f7pZX5kaI2oi53UvS5NU2kIf64i_UUL8-V6spyb59b9vVyeyTbktQjs_R9SqiJWe2rUiVnpqQUy-5wnWLj2_yyygXhTR2_LxjdGfl-Kcm4wY_RETgyYopap7CMuCuaT6HP2FdgAnikscxCbGlSQpLIopQklIhaq3LesBCkLp_pZ-2bLY9ahaXziF9or-jCYLGDJF9oOrxBW4t6bQ3K_B6uMHeC23k694hQWlJQGXKBJzG9SjdTK1UDOB10rB-vVoQj78TzRaItCF0q4Wn_3shu26Yo6rq5VxARNDWrn8hftoPOd9nMX3krKGNwp9BsjRoiD1KhN1oVsUIFxRwxJAT6gbJqN3zbfgh7TqWjo